During a meeting at the Europa Building in Brussels, President Michel and President Biden expressed their satisfaction with the strong unity and cooperation between the European Union and the United States. They emphasized the importance of taking intelligent decisions for future security and stability, especially in challenging times. President Biden commended President Michel on his re-election and stressed the need for unity among Western democracies. He highlighted his concerns about Vladimir Putin's intentions and his efforts to undermine democracies. President Biden also expressed his commitment to building total unity among major democracies and preventing the breakup of NATO. He thanked President Michel for his focus on the unity of Europe as a whole. When asked about China, President Biden confirmed that he had spent time with Xi Jinping and expressed his intention to discuss the matter further.